        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer22380385" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7848248607710215857">This is a clean even eloquent collection of poems that somehow didn&apos;t move me as much as it ought to have. I am willing to admit the fault to be in myself. Sometimes wonderful books come to us at the wrong time.<br/><br/>The book has three sections: Divorce Epistles, Breaking Up the House, and Late Wife. The last section, mostly loosely rhymed sonnets, is haunted by the ghost of the lover&apos;s late wife. This is the section that spoke most to me, though I read it in a noisey cafeteria. <br/><br/><i>For a long time there </i></span>
  <span id="freeText7848248607710215857" style="display:none">This is a clean even eloquent collection of poems that somehow didn't move me as much as it ought to have. I am willing to admit the fault to be in myself. Sometimes wonderful books come to us at the wrong time.<br /><br />The book has three sections: Divorce Epistles, Breaking Up the House, and Late Wife. The last section, mostly loosely rhymed sonnets, is haunted by the ghost of the lover's late wife. This is the section that spoke most to me, though I read it in a noisey cafeteria. <br /><br /><i>For a long time there would be the small<br />resurfacing of things you had forgotten<br />to throw away, or ceased to see at all.<br />These returned her, not to you, but to me<br />the way I had seen a spider unknot itself...</i><br /><br />-- from "Corrective"</span>
