<span id="freeTextContainer9549675588118806666">Late Wife by Claudia Emerson offers a beautiful collection of poems formatted similarly to a short story. Each poem ebbs and flows into the next, depicting both dramatic and enthralling situations from her own life. Beginning with â€œNatural History Exhibitsâ€ which captures the guilt of a failed marriage, she illuminates the stage for the first section â€œDivorce Epistlesâ€. She uses not only language but also the format of her poems to illustrate profound emotion. The poems found in â€œDivorce Epistle</span>
  <span id="freeText9549675588118806666" style="display:none">Late Wife by Claudia Emerson offers a beautiful collection of poems formatted similarly to a short story. Each poem ebbs and flows into the next, depicting both dramatic and enthralling situations from her own life. Beginning with â€œNatural History Exhibitsâ€ which captures the guilt of a failed marriage, she illuminates the stage for the first section â€œDivorce Epistlesâ€. She uses not only language but also the format of her poems to illustrate profound emotion. The poems found in â€œDivorce Epistlesâ€ and â€œBreaking Up The Houseâ€ are choppy and confusing to the eyes but as you read into â€œLetters To Kentâ€ they transform into sonnet formation mostly. This could be because sonnets are romanticized and she has high hopes for the success of her next marriage. </span>
